WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:01:47.362 --> 00:01:51.039
Mom! Jethro's eating my underwear!

3
00:01:54.562 --> 00:01:57.115
Here. piggy. piggy. piggy. Jethro.

4
00:01:57.345 --> 00:01:59.997
Mom. before she starts.
there isn't a shred of evidence

5
00:02:00.099 --> 00:02:03.394
- to support her allegations.
- Gillian. your son is a psycho.

6
00:02:03.490 --> 00:02:08.031
- He booby-trapped my hair dryer.
- Nice hypothesis. but you can't prove it.

7
00:02:08.259 --> 00:02:12.667
- Yeah. but I can hurt you.
- Mom! Mom! She needs to be medicated.

8
00:02:12.964 --> 00:02:15.003
- Come on. Jethro.
- Come here.

9
00:02:16.130 --> 00:02:18.978
I hate this family. Come here.

10
00:02:20.099 --> 00:02:22.433
Jethro. you're getting a time out.

11
00:02:34.435 --> 00:02:37.370
Come on. guys. Backpack.

12
00:02:42.114 --> 00:02:45.912
- What? It's in style.
- It's inappropriate. Go put on some jeans.

13
00:02:47.523 --> 00:02:49.215
And spit out the gum.

14
00:02:51.268 --> 00:02:53.635
So. what color do you want to wear today?

15
00:02:53.860 --> 00:02:57.090
Red? Blue? Purple?

16
00:02:57.412 --> 00:02:59.200
Pink. Momma. pink.

17
00:02:59.843 --> 00:03:02.691
- Farren.
- What? You said jeans.

18
00:03:03.620 --> 00:03:05.628
I meant in your size.

19
00:03:07.812 --> 00:03:11.555
Come on. guys. Come on.
We don't want to be late. There you go.

20
00:03:15.780 --> 00:03:17.341
Come on. sweetie.

21
00:03:20.612 --> 00:03:22.435
- No!
- Get out!

22
00:03:25.093 --> 00:03:26.402
No fighting.

23
00:03:38.341 --> 00:03:39.518
Allow me.

24
00:03:39.749 --> 00:03:40.960
- Hi.
- Hi.

25
00:03:41.061 --> 00:03:43.811
- Are we still on for dinner?
- I'll be there.

26
00:03:44.645 --> 00:03:46.304
We have an audience.

27
00:03:46.661 --> 00:03:50.077
- Yuck. I'm going to vomit.
- He is such a loser.

28
00:03:50.181 --> 00:03:52.036
I like Bob. He's nice.

29
00:03:52.132 --> 00:03:55.067
He's a boring pen importer.
He does the same routine every day.

30
00:03:55.173 --> 00:03:57.922
- He's like a robot.
- That's 'cause he is a robot.

31
00:03:58.021 --> 00:04:02.692
A cyborg. sent from the future.
to destroy humanity. Starting with us.

32
00:04:06.917 --> 00:04:10.049
Well. it's been three months.
Happy anniversary.

33
00:04:17.093 --> 00:04:18.370
What is it?

34
00:04:20.742 --> 00:04:23.043
I have to tell you about my job.

35
00:04:24.901 --> 00:04:26.625
This might shock you.

36
00:04:27.270 --> 00:04:31.328
but you should know everything
before this relationship goes further.

37
00:04:32.325 --> 00:04:33.919
- Don't. Bob.
- What?

38
00:04:35.943 --> 00:04:38.244
I'm very happy when I'm with you.

39
00:04:38.439 --> 00:04:41.090
No one has ever made me laugh like you do.

40
00:04:41.479 --> 00:04:44.162
and if I were a single woman.
I could see a real future for us.

41
00:04:44.263 --> 00:04:46.150
But I'm a package deal.

42
00:04:47.015 --> 00:04:48.541
What do you mean?

43
00:04:49.383 --> 00:04:53.180
My kids are my priority and...
How can I put this gently?

44
00:04:53.831 --> 00:04:56.219
- They hate me.
- Yeah.

45
00:04:56.838 --> 00:04:59.522
- I can make them like me.
- See?

46
00:04:59.624 --> 00:05:02.852
You can't make kids like you.
not mine or anyone's.

47
00:05:05.094 --> 00:05:07.648
My kids have been through a lot. and...

48
00:05:07.782 --> 00:05:11.840
I don't think we should take the next step
until they warm up to you.

49
00:05:12.457 --> 00:05:14.561
Doesn't your happiness count?

50
00:05:16.744 --> 00:05:18.019
Excuse me.

51
00:05:21.832 --> 00:05:24.865
Sorry. I gotta go. Emergency at work.

52
00:05:25.353 --> 00:05:27.937
- No ink?
- It's much bigger.

53
00:05:28.488 --> 00:05:31.521
Sorry. really.
I will explain everything tomorrow.

54
00:05:32.872 --> 00:05:34.879
Okay. I'll see you tomorrow.

55
00:05:54.216 --> 00:05:55.940
- What took you so long to get here?
- Six minutes.

56
00:05:56.040 --> 00:05:58.561
- You stop for a latte?
- I get it. You're...

57
00:05:58.697 --> 00:06:01.828
- What's the expression? Chopping my bust.
- Close enough.

58
00:06:01.929 --> 00:06:05.028
Poldark and a couple other Russkys
just went in the refinery.

59
00:06:05.992 --> 00:06:08.775
Then I was right. He's planning something.

60
00:06:09.544 --> 00:06:11.170
Maybe they just want to fill up
their gas tanks for free.

61
00:06:11.273 --> 00:06:13.412
- I couldn't blame them.
- No. that man's so crooked.

62
00:06:13.512 --> 00:06:15.814
he could eat nails and poop corkscrews.

63
00:06:15.912 --> 00:06:17.375
You're the world's foremost authority
on Poldark.

64
00:06:17.481 --> 00:06:18.758
What do you think he's up to?

65
00:06:18.857 --> 00:06:21.312
If his mission is to sabotage
the world's oil reserves.

66
00:06:21.417 --> 00:06:24.352
why would he care about
some two-bit refinery like this one?

67
00:06:24.840 --> 00:06:27.524
I'll make sure you get a chance to ask him.

68
00:06:41.737 --> 00:06:44.520
How the heck are you going to get in there?
A jet pack?

69
00:06:44.874 --> 00:06:46.401
It's in the shop.

70
00:07:02.186 --> 00:07:03.942
Wait for my signal.

71
00:07:12.073 --> 00:07:13.219
Yuri.

72
00:07:14.603 --> 00:07:16.293
- What's this?
- C-4.

73
00:07:16.586 --> 00:07:20.547
When we are done here. I want you
to blow this place to smithereens.

74
00:07:55.531 --> 00:07:59.524
Hurry up. I don't have all day.
There is no overtime here.

75
00:08:21.292 --> 00:08:22.885
Bob Ho.

76
00:08:35.980 --> 00:08:38.534
I would love to chat. but I gotta go.

77
00:09:24.238 --> 00:09:26.539
- Up there. Go. go. go. go.
- Move it.

78
00:09:26.669 --> 00:09:28.556
- Move.
- Hold it. Stay where you are.

79
00:09:28.685 --> 00:09:32.035
That was fun. A good aerobic workout.

80
00:09:33.838 --> 00:09:36.107
We should do this again sometime.

81
00:09:36.303 --> 00:09:37.928
Okay. Poldark. let's go.

82
00:09:38.766 --> 00:09:40.741
<i>We have suspect in custody.</i>

83
00:09:43.599 --> 00:09:46.381
Did you see the look
on Poldark's face. man?

84
00:09:48.782 --> 00:09:51.116
Brilliant work. Bob. Unbelievable.

85
00:09:51.342 --> 00:09:53.992
I really hate to see you go home.
You're the best agent I've ever had.

86
00:09:54.222 --> 00:09:56.523
Hey. you know I'm standing right here.

87
00:09:56.623 --> 00:09:59.372
Maybe I can get your government
to loan you to me just a little bit longer.

88
00:09:59.469 --> 00:10:03.147
No. This was my last assignment.
I'm retiring.

89
00:10:03.791 --> 00:10:08.974
- Don't tell me because of Gillian.
- I want a normal life. I want to get married.

90
00:10:09.551 --> 00:10:11.209
Oh. heck. man. Don't get married.

91
00:10:11.311 --> 00:10:13.415
Just find some woman
that you're going to hate in five years

92
00:10:13.519 --> 00:10:15.374
and give her your house.

93
00:10:16.432 --> 00:10:19.944
Keep the watch.
A memento. compliments of the CIA.

94
00:10:21.392 --> 00:10:23.726
So. Gillian? Is that the woman
that lives next door to your cover house?

95
00:10:23.822 --> 00:10:27.532
- Yeah. they've been stepping out.
- I could never give up this life for a woman.

96
00:10:27.696 --> 00:10:28.743
We're spies. man.

97
00:10:28.847 --> 00:10:31.367
Every little boy wants to be a spy.
It's the life.

98
00:10:31.471 --> 00:10:33.991
All the hours you spend
sitting alone in a little room like this.

99
00:10:34.094 --> 00:10:36.299
eating cold take-out food
in the back of a surveillance van.

100
00:10:36.399 --> 00:10:37.861
getting shot at all the time.

101
00:10:37.967 --> 00:10:40.422
learning how to pee in a bottle
in a moving vehicle.

102
00:10:40.880 --> 00:10:44.556
- You're doing the right thing.
- Only problem is that her kids hate me.

103
00:10:46.415 --> 00:10:47.878
You the man.

104
00:10:48.336 --> 00:10:50.440
Really gonna miss you. Ho.
Good luck with those kids.

105
00:10:50.544 --> 00:10:53.960
I've brought down dictators.
How tough can three kids be?

106
00:10:56.048 --> 00:10:57.357
- Come on. Ringo. come on.
- Here. kitty. kitty. kitty.

107
00:10:57.456 --> 00:11:00.271
- Ringo!
- Don't worry. Come on. Come on.

108
00:11:00.368 --> 00:11:02.343
- Come on. Right here.
- Come on. Ringo.

109
00:11:02.479 --> 00:11:03.887
- Come on. Ringo.
- Ringo.

110
00:11:03.984 --> 00:11:05.161
Hi. kids.

111
00:11:10.128 --> 00:11:12.779
I'm sorry about running out last night.

112
00:11:13.073 --> 00:11:15.941
- It's all right. It's your job.
- No. it was rude.

113
00:11:16.048 --> 00:11:18.535
I promise it will never happen again.

114
00:11:19.055 --> 00:11:21.391
Mom. what about Ringo?

115
00:11:22.737 --> 00:11:26.699
We've tried everything. sweetheart.
He'll come down when he's ready.

116
00:11:27.952 --> 00:11:29.098
You want to see
what I've been working on?

117
00:11:29.201 --> 00:11:30.445
Sure.

118
00:11:32.082 --> 00:11:36.521
Ringo. Ringo! Come on. kitty.
It's not that far.

119
00:11:36.816 --> 00:11:39.206
Please. please. please. Ringo.

120
00:11:46.289 --> 00:11:47.696
There you go.

121
00:12:02.130 --> 00:12:04.716
- So. what do you think?
- Well...

122
00:12:07.314 --> 00:12:08.688
It's a work-in-progress.

123
00:12:08.785 --> 00:12:10.990
Sadly. I didn't have any time
to work on it today.

124
00:12:11.154 --> 00:12:13.324
Cat was on the roof.
satellite's broken again.

125
00:12:13.426 --> 00:12:16.458
I spent two hours on hold
trying to get a repairman out here.

126
00:12:16.594 --> 00:12:19.594
and I can't stop thinking about last night.

127
00:12:20.241 --> 00:12:22.924
So. are we okay?

128
00:12:24.402 --> 00:12:26.158
I understand.

129
00:12:26.258 --> 00:12:29.323
If a man marries you.
he marries all four of you.

130
00:12:30.226 --> 00:12:33.193
Don't forget the pig. the cat and the turtle.

131
00:12:34.802 --> 00:12:37.453
So. do you really like it?

132
00:12:38.099 --> 00:12:39.920
It frightens me.

133
00:12:40.562 --> 00:12:44.338
Sometimes I think I found
the last honest man left in the world.

134
00:12:54.066 --> 00:12:56.336
I brought you all cookies.

135
00:12:59.346 --> 00:13:01.898
- Yes?
- Is it true? You're going to marry Bob?

136
00:13:02.066 --> 00:13:05.002
- What? Whoa! Calm down.
- You can't do this. Gillian.

137
00:13:05.106 --> 00:13:06.568
You're. like. so far above him.

138
00:13:06.674 --> 00:13:09.490
What she means is he's boring. He's a geek.

139
00:13:09.587 --> 00:13:12.435
He's a very nice man
who treats me very well.

140
00:13:12.627 --> 00:13:16.174
- He's a pen importer.
- He's a cyborg.

141
00:13:17.747 --> 00:13:20.016
You all don't know him like I do.

142
00:13:20.115 --> 00:13:23.017
He's very passionate about the world
and about my art.

143
00:13:23.156 --> 00:13:26.417
He likes to talk about history.
science and politics.

144
00:13:27.251 --> 00:13:30.154
I see what you mean about
him not being boring.

145
00:13:32.755 --> 00:13:36.072
What you all call boring. I call dependable.

146
00:13:36.308 --> 00:13:39.373
For once. I'd like a man who goes to work
every day at the same time.

147
00:13:39.571 --> 00:13:41.514
and who comes home every single night.

148
00:13:41.685 --> 00:13:46.026
A man who doesn't lie. or cheat.
or leave his family the first time some...

149
00:13:56.213 --> 00:13:58.100
My happiness counts. too.

150
00:14:01.109 --> 00:14:03.344
I hate it when old people have feelings.

151
00:14:05.300 --> 00:14:07.089
We gotta deep-six Bob.

152
00:14:20.629 --> 00:14:23.312
- What's the story here?
- They hit Poldark's prison transport caravan

153
00:14:23.412 --> 00:14:26.131
- at the edge of town.
- Tell me he didn't get away.

154
00:14:26.486 --> 00:14:29.071
He's as gone as rum cake at an AA meeting.

155
00:14:29.174 --> 00:14:30.548
I'm telling you.
this whole thing was a setup.

156
00:14:30.645 --> 00:14:32.271
They knew he was coming.

157
00:14:34.070 --> 00:14:35.695
Are you saying
there's a mole in the agency?

158
00:14:35.797 --> 00:14:38.480
I'm not saying anything except he got away.

159
00:14:57.109 --> 00:14:58.484
Welcome back.

160
00:15:09.334 --> 00:15:13.394
Tatiana.
you can't imagine what it's like in there.

161
00:15:13.622 --> 00:15:18.194
The oppressive darkness and the torture
of empty days stretching for years.

162
00:15:18.806 --> 00:15:22.154
- Prison is hell.
- You were in there for four hours.

163
00:15:22.966 --> 00:15:24.755
Enough tearful reunion.

164
00:15:27.286 --> 00:15:30.548
I need a new batch of the formula
as soon as possible.

165
00:15:31.798 --> 00:15:34.165
We'll run another test in two days.

166
00:15:35.862 --> 00:15:39.508
I need a change of clothes.
Something current and fashionable.

167
00:15:39.895 --> 00:15:42.994
And something to eat
that does not come with a toy.

168
00:16:17.400 --> 00:16:20.149
<i>The Sea Hag's made Olive into a zombie.</i>

169
00:16:43.001 --> 00:16:44.822
Honey. we're getting ready
to carve pumpkins downstairs.

170
00:16:44.920 --> 00:16:46.708
- You want to join us?
- Absolutely!

171
00:16:46.808 --> 00:16:49.842
'Cause I'm a loser and I have no life.

172
00:16:50.008 --> 00:16:53.205
Did I mention we're going
to toast the pumpkin seeds?

173
00:16:53.881 --> 00:16:56.751
Come on. I want you to join the family.

174
00:16:56.857 --> 00:16:58.646
And I want some privacy.

175
00:16:58.745 --> 00:17:00.819
- Don't get fresh with me.
- I'll use whatever tone of voice

176
00:17:00.921 --> 00:17:03.671
- I want to use with you.
- Farren. I want you downstairs...

177
00:17:03.769 --> 00:17:05.263
No. I'm not going to come downstairs
right now. Get out.

178
00:17:05.368 --> 00:17:07.376
Farren. this is my house.
You will listen to me.

179
00:17:07.482 --> 00:17:10.547
You don't own me. Get out.
I said. get out. Gillian. Get out!

180
00:17:10.649 --> 00:17:12.143
Downstairs in five minutes.

181
00:17:12.249 --> 00:17:15.217
I hate this house. I hate this family. Get out!

182
00:17:22.297 --> 00:17:23.606
<i>Me spinach!</i>

183
00:17:27.193 --> 00:17:29.682
No. she won't hear me. I'm on the roof.

184
00:17:30.298 --> 00:17:34.095
It's like the only place
I can get any privacy in this loony bin.

185
00:17:34.778 --> 00:17:37.166
I can't let Gillian marry this guy.

186
00:17:38.010 --> 00:17:41.141
No. it's not that.
I mean. you're right. he is a total drone.

187
00:17:41.242 --> 00:17:43.216
but that's not the issue.

188
00:17:43.321 --> 00:17:45.143
What's going to happen
when my dad comes back?

189
00:17:46.458 --> 00:17:48.913
He won't just leave me here alone.
He'll be back.

190
00:17:49.019 --> 00:17:52.947
And if she's married. what happens then?
I don't know.

191
00:18:01.850 --> 00:18:04.239
Mom. lan's feeding Jethro bacon.

192
00:18:04.474 --> 00:18:07.159
- Okay. that's just wrong.
- Why is it wrong?

193
00:18:21.947 --> 00:18:25.559
- Ho. Bob Ho.
- Hey. So. how's it going with those kids?

194
00:18:25.819 --> 00:18:27.728
I'm taking Gillian and the children
on a picnic.

195
00:18:27.834 --> 00:18:29.689
I'm going to force those kids to like me.

196
00:18:29.787 --> 00:18:33.846
Force them? You know. you might as well
try scratching your ear with your elbow.

197
00:18:34.747 --> 00:18:37.268
Guess what? Poldark escaped.

198
00:18:40.859 --> 00:18:45.050
- No longer my problem.
<i>- Yeah. I know. but we recovered a file.</i>

199
00:18:45.244 --> 00:18:47.731
It seems to be an entry portal to a website.

200
00:18:47.899 --> 00:18:50.770
<i>We can't crack it.</i>
<i>I thought maybe you could take a look at it.</i>

201
00:18:51.069 --> 00:18:54.614
Hey. if you can figure it out. great.
If you can't. no harm. no foul.

202
00:18:56.156 --> 00:18:59.189
As a favor to you.
Send it to my home computer.

203
00:18:59.324 --> 00:19:00.752
<i>Already did.</i>

204
00:19:01.339 --> 00:19:06.161
While I'm thinking about it. they suspect
there may be a mole at the agency.

205
00:19:06.491 --> 00:19:08.531
- They suspect me?
<i>- No.</i>

206
00:19:08.635 --> 00:19:12.182
You know Glaze thinks
you're the sharpest barb on the wire.

207
00:19:12.476 --> 00:19:14.385
I have no idea what that means.

208
00:19:15.035 --> 00:19:16.978
Hey. listen. man. have fun on your picnic.

209
00:19:17.085 --> 00:19:20.467
Just shoot me back
when you check out that file. Thanks.

210
00:19:36.829 --> 00:19:40.124
Puzzle encryption.
Let's see what you've got.

211
00:19:54.845 --> 00:19:57.497
- Is it noon already?
- No. I have bad news.

212
00:20:00.190 --> 00:20:03.124
- My father is in the hospital.
- That's terrible.

213
00:20:03.678 --> 00:20:05.652
He plays senior softball
and he slid into third.

214
00:20:05.757 --> 00:20:08.627
- Now he's having his hip replaced.
- That's terrible.

215
00:20:08.733 --> 00:20:12.442
I have to leave the kids
and fly to Denver to take care of Dad.

216
00:20:13.341 --> 00:20:16.059
- That's great.
- What are you talking about?

217
00:20:16.221 --> 00:20:17.465
Let me watch the kids.

218
00:20:17.566 --> 00:20:20.665
It would give us a chance
to get to know each other.

219
00:20:20.766 --> 00:20:25.042
No. Bob. You? Them? I don't know.

220
00:20:25.373 --> 00:20:28.407
My aunt's flying in from San Antonio.
She's very good with the kids.

221
00:20:28.510 --> 00:20:32.220
- She was in the military.
- Gillian. this could be just what we need.

222
00:20:32.382 --> 00:20:34.619
You really think you can handle
that kind of pressure?

223
00:20:34.975 --> 00:20:37.691
The driving. the schoolwork.
and then there's Halloween.

224
00:20:37.854 --> 00:20:40.222
Getting their costumes.
finishing decorating the house?

225
00:20:40.319 --> 00:20:43.253
No problem. Halloween is my favorite.

226
00:20:43.454 --> 00:20:46.586
You have nothing to worry about.
They will be perfectly safe with me.

227
00:20:48.063 --> 00:20:50.266
It's not them I'm worried about.

228
00:20:52.351 --> 00:20:55.285
- You can't be serious.
- Isn't there any other option?

229
00:20:55.390 --> 00:20:57.299
Foster care? Juvenile hall?

230
00:20:58.752 --> 00:21:00.539
Okay. You'll be fine.

231
00:21:01.246 --> 00:21:02.872
Love you guys.

232
00:21:05.021 --> 00:21:08.186
- I'm going to miss you.
- Yeah. as proven by this total abandonment.

233
00:21:08.286 --> 00:21:11.703
You'll survive. I'll buy you something
from the hospital gift shop.

234
00:21:11.807 --> 00:21:13.302
- Bye.
- Bye. Love you.

235
00:21:13.407 --> 00:21:15.414
- See you later.
- Bye.

236
00:21:20.192 --> 00:21:22.711
So. is this exciting. or what?

237
00:21:25.600 --> 00:21:29.909
Well. I'll just pack a few things.
and we'll go to your house. okay?

238
00:21:42.047 --> 00:21:44.503
A Flowbee. I knew he cut his own hair.

239
00:21:44.672 --> 00:21:46.975
Nothing telling in his DVD collection.

240
00:21:47.072 --> 00:21:49.755
Standard action movies.
mainstream comedies.

241
00:21:49.856 --> 00:21:52.573
no sci-fi. and nothing above PG-13.

242
00:21:54.529 --> 00:21:56.919
Hey. his computer. Let's check it out.

243
00:21:57.025 --> 00:21:59.446
Good idea.
There's got to be some dirt on there.

244
00:22:03.361 --> 00:22:05.532
Fashion Armageddon.

245
00:22:05.633 --> 00:22:08.829
I haven't forgotten. Colton.
I will look at the file.

246
00:22:08.960 --> 00:22:12.277
But this is important. What is Halloween?

247
00:22:14.593 --> 00:22:17.692
Farren. do you realize what this is?

248
00:22:18.273 --> 00:22:21.469
It's got you all worked up.
Let me guess. a Klingon dictionary?

249
00:22:21.568 --> 00:22:24.886
You have me confused
with an entirely different class of geek.

250
00:22:24.993 --> 00:22:26.401
Stockholm GBH.

251
00:22:26.497 --> 00:22:29.727
Grievous Bodily Harm. live in Stockholm.

252
00:22:29.922 --> 00:22:32.987
This is one of the rarest bootleg concerts
in the world.

253
00:22:33.122 --> 00:22:36.504
- Why does Bob have it?
- Who cares? I'm gonna download it.

254
00:22:38.530 --> 00:22:41.180
This is my ticket to Coolsville.

255
00:22:49.953 --> 00:22:52.255
