256
00:22:53.697 --> 00:22:55.454
You said you wanted current.

257
00:22:55.554 --> 00:22:57.942
I look like the Fresh Prince of Belarus.

258
00:22:58.048 --> 00:23:00.832
Send someone out
to get me something elegant.

259
00:23:01.155 --> 00:23:03.325
What is this program you found?

260
00:23:03.747 --> 00:23:05.405
I went on to download the formula

261
00:23:05.506 --> 00:23:08.541
and found the site being accessed
by a third party.

262
00:23:08.738 --> 00:23:11.008
If the United States or China
has the formula.

263
00:23:11.106 --> 00:23:12.480
they can develop an antibody for it.

264
00:23:12.578 --> 00:23:14.880
I'm tracing the ISP.
but it's heavily encrypted.

265
00:23:14.979 --> 00:23:17.082
It will take me a while to track it down.

266
00:23:17.187 --> 00:23:19.739
Find whoever downloaded my formula.

267
00:23:20.194 --> 00:23:22.649
- Retrieve it.
- And?

268
00:23:23.521 --> 00:23:26.042
- Kill them.
- Thank you.

269
00:23:33.826 --> 00:23:35.801
- What's up with you?
- I'm gonna kill you.

270
00:23:35.971 --> 00:23:37.826
What? I'm gonna kill you.

271
00:23:38.371 --> 00:23:40.705
Don't hurt me! Don't hurt me!
She's hurting me!

272
00:23:40.803 --> 00:23:42.690
Hey. hey. hey.

273
00:23:44.003 --> 00:23:45.280
Hey. stop!

274
00:23:45.795 --> 00:23:48.643
- What's going on here?
- She threw a stink bomb in my room.

275
00:23:48.739 --> 00:23:50.080
What? That's so not true.

276
00:23:50.179 --> 00:23:53.977
So what. you're saying I threw
a stink bomb in my own room

277
00:23:54.180 --> 00:23:57.627
just to get you in trouble? Sad. So sad.

278
00:23:57.795 --> 00:23:59.322
Hey. hey. hey.

279
00:24:00.068 --> 00:24:02.522
Farren. I'm very disappointed in you.

280
00:24:03.875 --> 00:24:05.698
You two should be in bed by now.

281
00:24:05.796 --> 00:24:09.243
Well. if we finish our homework in time.
Gillian lets us stay up till midnight.

282
00:24:11.266 --> 00:24:15.042
She also likes us to watch Adult Swim.
It's kind of a tradition.

283
00:24:16.067 --> 00:24:18.621
I didn't really think this one through.

284
00:24:27.524 --> 00:24:31.004
Nora. let's get ready for bed.

285
00:24:31.396 --> 00:24:33.306
I don't want to go to bed.

286
00:24:38.148 --> 00:24:40.482
Only my mommy can dress me.

287
00:24:41.027 --> 00:24:42.173
Nora.

288
00:24:45.413 --> 00:24:46.722
Here I come.

289
00:24:47.876 --> 00:24:51.652
Hey! Come back. I'll get you.

290
00:24:53.446 --> 00:24:55.201
Come back!

291
00:24:57.637 --> 00:24:59.546
I got you. No. come back!

292
00:25:04.133 --> 00:25:05.148
Nora.

293
00:25:06.149 --> 00:25:08.090
Come on. Nora.

294
00:25:09.413 --> 00:25:11.170
- Only my mommy can dress me.
- Come on. Nora.

295
00:25:11.269 --> 00:25:13.408
Only my mommy can dress me!

296
00:25:14.020 --> 00:25:16.410
Only mommy can dress me!

297
00:25:17.669 --> 00:25:18.846
You.

298
00:25:25.061 --> 00:25:27.844
Can your mommy do that? Sleep.

299
00:25:53.670 --> 00:25:54.980
Get out!

300
00:26:01.638 --> 00:26:05.087
- Hello?
- You're alive. That's a good sign.

301
00:26:05.574 --> 00:26:09.405
- How are the kids?
- We had a great night. Easy as pie.

302
00:26:10.279 --> 00:26:12.897
Really? You're with my kids. right?

303
00:26:14.440 --> 00:26:16.960
Bob. the other night at dinner.

304
00:26:17.063 --> 00:26:20.773
you were gonna say something
about your job. and I cut you off.

305
00:26:21.448 --> 00:26:23.454
You want to tell me now?

306
00:26:24.743 --> 00:26:26.947
It can wait until you get back.

307
00:26:28.583 --> 00:26:33.220
- I really think this was a good idea.
- I'm sure the worst is behind us.

308
00:26:51.880 --> 00:26:53.287
Just a second.

309
00:27:13.448 --> 00:27:14.724
I got it.

310
00:27:16.777 --> 00:27:17.954
Fire!

311
00:27:24.232 --> 00:27:25.640
Big mistake.

312
00:27:30.952 --> 00:27:33.799
Everything will be fine. Oatmeal's ready.

313
00:27:40.042 --> 00:27:42.081
- Shotgun.
- It's not your day.

314
00:27:42.505 --> 00:27:44.577
You sure your mother
lets you go to school like that?

315
00:27:44.681 --> 00:27:45.859
Duh. Bob.

316
00:27:46.889 --> 00:27:48.067
"Duh. Bob."

317
00:27:59.626 --> 00:28:02.495
- Bye.
- Well. you guys have a nice day.

318
00:28:05.514 --> 00:28:08.098
- Hi.
- That is so cute.

319
00:28:11.274 --> 00:28:13.412
So what do you do all day?

320
00:28:14.057 --> 00:28:15.617
Nothing. I'm four.

321
00:28:22.665 --> 00:28:24.454
- You're full of it.
- Yeah. full of it.

322
00:28:24.555 --> 00:28:26.942
I'm telling you. I downloaded it yesterday.

323
00:28:27.049 --> 00:28:29.286
Really? 'Cause if you really had.
that'd be pretty cool.

324
00:28:29.387 --> 00:28:31.940
- Yeah. pretty cool.
- Let's hear it then.

325
00:28:37.579 --> 00:28:40.000
You trying to pop our ears?
That's nothing but a bunch of static.

326
00:28:40.106 --> 00:28:41.514
- I don't get it.
- I get it.

327
00:28:41.610 --> 00:28:44.458
You're a pathetic little nerd and a liar.
Let's get him.

328
00:28:45.515 --> 00:28:47.457
Wedgie!

329
00:28:47.562 --> 00:28:50.410
Put me down! Put me down!
Put me down! Put me down!

330
00:28:50.507 --> 00:28:52.295
Okay. you asked for it.

331
00:28:55.755 --> 00:28:58.788
No! You guys are gonna hear from me
and my lawyer.

332
00:28:59.178 --> 00:29:02.593
You'll pay for this.
each and every one of you.

333
00:29:09.835 --> 00:29:12.202
So. tell me more about Halloween.

334
00:29:13.195 --> 00:29:15.781
It's the best. You get candy.

335
00:29:16.364 --> 00:29:20.641
Everyone pretends to be someone else.
and nobody knows who you really are.

336
00:29:21.036 --> 00:29:23.687
Sounds familiar. Nora...

337
00:29:25.067 --> 00:29:28.581
So. what do you want to be?
A Frankenstein? A zombie?

338
00:29:29.707 --> 00:29:32.228
Sweetie. do you want to be a princess?

339
00:29:33.739 --> 00:29:34.852
Yes.

340
00:29:40.140 --> 00:29:42.049
Okay. princess.

341
00:29:46.636 --> 00:29:47.750
Nora?

342
00:29:51.212 --> 00:29:55.489
Not fairy. Princess. Princess.

343
00:29:56.748 --> 00:29:57.926
Princess.

344
00:30:02.700 --> 00:30:04.009
Pink.

345
00:30:05.164 --> 00:30:06.179
Pink.

346
00:30:24.621 --> 00:30:27.370
- Princess.
- It's too big.

347
00:30:28.365 --> 00:30:31.364
Too big? Okay.

348
00:30:44.429 --> 00:30:46.949
Nora? Nora.

349
00:30:50.444 --> 00:30:51.623
Nora.

350
00:30:56.077 --> 00:30:57.092
Nora.

351
00:31:01.197 --> 00:31:02.375
Nora.

352
00:31:06.478 --> 00:31:07.590
Nora!

353
00:31:12.303 --> 00:31:15.531
Nora. I'm sorry. Sorry. Sorry.

354
00:31:20.910 --> 00:31:22.055
Nora!

355
00:31:42.704 --> 00:31:45.551
Nora. Please don't wander off again.

356
00:31:46.447 --> 00:31:47.875
I'm sorry. Bob.

357
00:31:48.911 --> 00:31:50.984
Let's go pay for your costume.

358
00:31:55.919 --> 00:31:57.228
Yo. it's Ho.

359
00:31:59.406 --> 00:32:01.577
Just hold him till I get there.

360
00:32:08.207 --> 00:32:12.365
Can I just say before we begin that
only in the current distressed condition

361
00:32:12.464 --> 00:32:14.733
of the American public school system

362
00:32:14.833 --> 00:32:18.476
could I be deposited headfirst
into a garbage can.

363
00:32:18.576 --> 00:32:22.286
and yet I'm the one who winds up
receiving disciplinary action?

364
00:32:23.760 --> 00:32:25.166
Who exactly are you?

365
00:32:26.383 --> 00:32:28.010
I'm his mother's...

366
00:32:29.616 --> 00:32:30.825
- Neighbor.
- Neighbor.

367
00:32:30.929 --> 00:32:33.547
I'm watching them for a few days.

368
00:32:34.161 --> 00:32:36.616
Well. this is not the first time
lan has been in trouble.

369
00:32:36.720 --> 00:32:38.508
He gets in fights. He lies.

370
00:32:38.608 --> 00:32:39.536
Hey. I don't lie.

371
00:32:39.631 --> 00:32:43.756
You told everyone you invited
Selena Gomez to the spring dance.

372
00:32:44.080 --> 00:32:45.868
Her appearance fee was an obstacle.

373
00:32:45.968 --> 00:32:48.424
You said you spent New Year's Eve
at the Playboy Mansion.

374
00:32:48.562 --> 00:32:51.692
Hey. pay-per-view high-def.
I felt like I was there.

375
00:32:57.553 --> 00:33:00.237
I'm telling you. lying is a dangerous game.

376
00:33:00.465 --> 00:33:02.832
Bob. you sell pens. What do you...

377
00:33:02.929 --> 00:33:05.164
- Oh. no. That's them.
- Who?

378
00:33:05.265 --> 00:33:08.047
The future felons who
put me in the trash can.

379
00:33:09.105 --> 00:33:11.439
Hey. geek-boy.
we got detention because of you.

380
00:33:11.537 --> 00:33:14.320
- Yeah. because of you.
- You're gonna pay for that.

381
00:33:14.417 --> 00:33:17.678
- Gentlemen. we don't want trouble.
- Who's this? Your mom?

382
00:33:17.872 --> 00:33:22.695
You wish. He's my bodyguard.
I hired him. You better watch out.

383
00:33:22.832 --> 00:33:24.841
- That true?
- No. He's joking.

384
00:33:25.522 --> 00:33:28.272
- I'm their babysitter.
- What are you gonna do?

385
00:33:28.689 --> 00:33:31.559
Ask you politely to allow us to pass.

386
00:33:43.249 --> 00:33:46.446
How humiliating.
Why didn't you do something?

387
00:33:47.154 --> 00:33:49.837
Why did you tell them
I was your bodyguard?

388
00:33:50.481 --> 00:33:53.516
You're right.
I guess it was too big a stretch.

389
00:34:05.971 --> 00:34:08.688
Hey. How you doing? I'm lan.

390
00:34:08.978 --> 00:34:12.427
If I told you. you had a beautiful body.
would you hold it against me?

391
00:34:15.411 --> 00:34:19.372
- At least you're not shy.
- I wanted to talk to her in the worst way.

392
00:34:20.627 --> 00:34:22.317
Mission accomplished.

393
00:34:26.194 --> 00:34:27.623
Come here.

394
00:34:28.722 --> 00:34:30.349
You look so pretty.

395
00:34:33.235 --> 00:34:35.787
Farren. I didn't know you did gymnastics.

396
00:34:35.890 --> 00:34:38.575
Why would you?
You don't know anything about me.

397
00:34:38.771 --> 00:34:42.830
You come over to hang out with Gillian.
and you never even talk to us.

398
00:34:43.508 --> 00:34:45.069
Come on. let's go.

399
00:34:46.707 --> 00:34:48.594
The woman's got a point.

400
00:34:55.028 --> 00:34:59.697
I don't know who you are sending out
to buy my clothes. but I want them killed.

401
00:35:01.011 --> 00:35:05.518
- You could go yourself.
- I'm the most wanted man in America.

402
00:35:06.067 --> 00:35:09.134
I cannot exactly browse
the racks of JCPenneys.

403
00:35:09.524 --> 00:35:13.485
Just give me something that will blend in.
Something extremely American.

404
00:35:13.587 --> 00:35:16.588
Sir. we are ready to run the test.

405
00:35:43.732 --> 00:35:45.041
Magnificent.

406
00:35:54.518 --> 00:35:58.576
She must have plastic in her shoes.
It will eat any petroleum product.

407
00:36:01.750 --> 00:36:03.505
We're working on that.

408
00:36:08.565 --> 00:36:10.060
What happened to the bacteria?

409
00:36:10.166 --> 00:36:13.549
They live as long as they feed.
Once the oil is gone. they disappear.

410
00:36:13.654 --> 00:36:15.541
Just like my Jimmy Choos.

411
00:36:24.341 --> 00:36:25.486
Come in.

412
00:36:30.838 --> 00:36:31.950
Listen. about today...

413
00:36:32.054 --> 00:36:35.218
You could have stood up for me. you know.
I have to face those guys.

414
00:36:35.319 --> 00:36:36.879
So face them.

415
00:36:36.982 --> 00:36:39.023
Unless you want
to spend the rest of your life

416
00:36:39.127 --> 00:36:41.101
with your head in the trash can.

417
00:36:41.207 --> 00:36:44.817
Thanks for the advice. Bob.
All my problems are solved.

418
00:36:52.855 --> 00:36:54.709
They assign this in middle school?

419
00:36:54.806 --> 00:36:56.978
No. that's my pleasure reading.

420
00:37:00.535 --> 00:37:01.909
You're smart.

421
00:37:02.998 --> 00:37:06.316
You have a lot going for you.
Why do you make things up?

422
00:37:06.424 --> 00:37:09.325
Girls aren't exactly
impressed by astrophysics.

423
00:37:09.911 --> 00:37:13.360
Given the resources.
I could design. build and launch a rocket

424
00:37:13.464 --> 00:37:17.108
that would accurately circumscribe
an orbit of the moon.

425
00:37:17.208 --> 00:37:21.779
But other guys can. you know.
throw a ball through a hoop.

426
00:37:24.184 --> 00:37:26.551
I don't want you to get in trouble.

427
00:37:27.223 --> 00:37:28.629
I'll make you a deal.

428
00:37:28.727 --> 00:37:30.899
If you try to tell the truth from now on.

429
00:37:31.000 --> 00:37:32.887
I won't tell your mother about today.

430
00:37:32.983 --> 00:37:34.193
Really?

431
00:37:34.296 --> 00:37:36.183
Dude. that's almost cool.

432
00:37:36.728 --> 00:37:39.028
You mean for a guy who sells pens?

433
00:37:45.305 --> 00:37:47.312
Come on. kids. time for bed.

434
00:37:48.760 --> 00:37:50.735
Come on. one more spoonful.

435
00:38:17.144 --> 00:38:18.158
Nora.

436
00:38:34.169 --> 00:38:37.170
This one I learned it in China
when I was young.

437
00:39:22.329 --> 00:39:24.915
It's me. I need your help.

438
00:39:36.891 --> 00:39:39.313
I had to make up
one heck of a yarn to get all this stuff.

439
00:39:39.419 --> 00:39:40.629
What did you tell them?

440
00:39:40.731 --> 00:39:43.665
Well. let's just say if I don't find some
weapons-grade uranium by dawn.

441
00:39:43.770 --> 00:39:46.586
I'm in trouble.
What do you need all this for?

442
00:39:46.683 --> 00:39:48.952
To get the kids ready for school.

443
00:39:49.691 --> 00:39:52.758
Well. it's like my mom always used to say
when she was stationed over in East Berlin.

444
00:39:52.859 --> 00:39:56.601
She'd say. "Spying is easy.
Parenting is hard." Good luck.

445
00:40:11.388 --> 00:40:12.697
Bring it on.

446
00:40:13.883 --> 00:40:17.146
Farren. you've been in there all morning!
Let me in!

447
00:40:17.661 --> 00:40:20.278
Farren. let me in.

448
00:40:21.020 --> 00:40:23.890
Farren. let me in.

449
00:40:25.660 --> 00:40:29.075
<i>Farren. you've been in there all morning!</i>
<i>Let me in!</i>

450
00:40:29.179 --> 00:40:30.293
<i>Farren.</i>

451
00:40:31.133 --> 00:40:32.114
Hey!

452
00:40:33.276 --> 00:40:34.966
I guess it's my turn.

453
00:40:37.468 --> 00:40:40.118
<i>And. Farren. please put on a longer skirt.</i>

454
00:40:45.085 --> 00:40:46.514
This means war.

455
00:41:02.428 --> 00:41:03.443
Nora?

456
00:41:18.045 --> 00:41:19.059
Nora.

457
00:41:21.245 --> 00:41:22.652
Stay with Bob.

458
00:41:31.518 --> 00:41:33.012
Come on. Nora.

459
00:42:02.335 --> 00:42:04.636
- Where is he?
- Hiding.

460
00:42:04.735 --> 00:42:07.419
He's probably going to trick us
into opening the door.

461
00:42:07.519 --> 00:42:09.275
Help me put this away?

462
00:42:21.215 --> 00:42:23.451
Lan. You know the rules.

463
00:42:24.415 --> 00:42:26.040
No soda upstairs.

464
00:42:26.142 --> 00:42:27.703
What? How did you...

465
00:42:49.663 --> 00:42:51.321
Breakfast is served.

466
00:42:52.384 --> 00:42:54.172
Wow!

467
00:42:55.840 --> 00:42:57.465
Nora. time for bed.

468
00:43:09.598 --> 00:43:10.973
Night-night.

469
00:43:14.081 --> 00:43:16.666
It's a school night. You should be asleep.

470
00:43:16.768 --> 00:43:18.678
How'd you find me?

471
00:43:18.786 --> 00:43:20.279
Call it a hunch.

472
00:43:33.825 --> 00:43:37.087
Why do you call your mother
Gillian instead of Mom?

473
00:43:37.185 --> 00:43:38.712
She's not my mom.

474
00:43:39.681 --> 00:43:41.207
What do you mean?

475
00:43:41.313 --> 00:43:43.550
My father was married before.

476
00:43:43.649 --> 00:43:45.624
and my real mom died when I was little.

477
00:43:45.728 --> 00:43:47.353
Gillian is just my stepmother.

478
00:43:47.457 --> 00:43:50.327
And lan and Nora
are just my half brother and sister.

479
00:43:50.434 --> 00:43:52.702
I'm like the freak of the family.

480
00:43:53.729 --> 00:43:55.998
It must have hurt your feelings when he left.

481
00:43:56.097 --> 00:43:57.788
He'll be back for me.

482
00:43:58.306 --> 00:43:59.767
I know he's not
the greatest dad in the world.

483
00:43:59.873 --> 00:44:03.321
but he loves me.
and he's not going to leave me here alone.

484
00:44:09.153 --> 00:44:10.299
Anyway.

485
00:44:10.402 --> 00:44:13.336
you should not climb the roof like this.
It's not safe.

486
00:44:13.441 --> 00:44:15.613
Please don't tell me I can't come up here.

487
00:44:15.714 --> 00:44:17.819
It's like the only place I can chill.

488
00:44:17.921 --> 00:44:21.182
Actually. I was going to
offer to build you a railing.

489
00:44:22.402 --> 00:44:24.922
Are you trying to bribe me into liking you?

490
00:44:25.026 --> 00:44:27.001
I just want you to be safe.

491
00:44:32.291 --> 00:44:34.265
Mind if I chill with you?

492
00:44:35.843 --> 00:44:37.501
It's a free country.

493
00:44:46.082 --> 00:44:47.609
Look at the star.

494
00:45:02.211 --> 00:45:05.178
Good news. We got an address.

495
00:45:08.324 --> 00:45:12.098
Good. Take some men.
Get that download back.

496
00:45:13.027 --> 00:45:14.272
Tatiana.

497
00:45:16.483 --> 00:45:17.912
No survivors.

498
00:45:21.347 --> 00:45:23.006
Hey. boss. You like?

499
00:45:29.027 --> 00:45:30.107
No like?

500
00:45:37.442 --> 00:45:39.996
May I make a couple
of fashion suggestions?

501
00:45:40.932 --> 00:45:44.608
Women don't like the shirt tucked in.
Mess up your hair.

502
00:45:45.731 --> 00:45:48.994
- You know about fashion?
- No. but I know women.

503
00:45:50.660 --> 00:45:54.304
Wear it like this.
It's cool. I saw it in a movie.

504
00:45:55.076 --> 00:45:58.939
What movie? <i>Octopussy?</i> This isn't 1985.

505
00:45:59.205 --> 00:46:02.074
- I almost forgot.
- What's this?

506
00:46:02.468 --> 00:46:05.633
- Iggy Pop and David Bowie in Shanghai.
- What?

507
00:46:05.733 --> 00:46:09.081
This is only about the hardest concert
to find in the world.

508
00:46:09.188 --> 00:46:12.188
I guarantee no one else
in the school district has it.

509
00:46:12.677 --> 00:46:15.774
- You downloaded this for me?
- Don't worry. I paid for it.

510
00:46:15.876 --> 00:46:19.173
- How'd you even know about it?
- Easy. I was there.

511
00:46:28.517 --> 00:46:31.650
Bob. you're getting too efficient.
We're half an hour early.

512
00:46:31.750 --> 00:46:33.178
You're welcome.

513
00:46:35.525 --> 00:46:37.052
Have a great day.

514
00:46:41.381 --> 00:46:44.578
- Hey. cool look. Aaron.
- Thanks. It's lan.

515
00:46:45.094 --> 00:46:46.271
Whatever.

516
00:47:11.430 --> 00:47:12.956
Have a great day.

517
00:47:13.862 --> 00:47:17.691
Look. the talk on the roof the other night
doesn't mean we're friends.

518
00:47:17.798 --> 00:47:19.041
God forbid.

519
00:47:40.038 --> 00:47:42.211
We're here. There is nobody around.

520
00:47:42.311 --> 00:47:47.046
<i>I found the computer. but the file was</i>
<i>downloaded to an external storage device.</i>

521
00:47:47.367 --> 00:47:48.928
I can't find that.

522
00:47:51.494 --> 00:47:54.145
I think I just figured out who lives here.

523
00:47:54.438 --> 00:47:55.846
<i>Agent Ho.</i>

524
00:48:06.951 --> 00:48:11.044
- Hello.
- You must stop shooting things. Antosha.

525
00:48:11.399 --> 00:48:14.499
I said it would be bad
if the CIA or Chinese had it.

526
00:48:14.920 --> 00:48:19.110
But he's both. Find him. but keep him alive.

527
00:48:19.847 --> 00:48:22.597
I need to know who else he's shown this to.

528
00:48:27.657 --> 00:48:31.333
Listen up. Now. Everyone in here.

529
00:48:33.577 --> 00:48:37.438
We must locate Chinese Intelligence agent.
Bob Ho.

530
00:48:37.991 --> 00:48:43.588
He is very tricky. The best at what he does.
He won't be easy to find.

531
00:48:44.136 --> 00:48:45.216
- Ms. Creel.
- Not now.

532
00:48:45.320 --> 00:48:49.892
Imagine you are Chinese. highly trained.
and you want to disappear.

533
00:48:49.993 --> 00:48:52.776
I see him climbing with
a bunch of skulls on a rope.

534
00:48:52.874 --> 00:48:56.899
Okay. he's not Conan the Barbarian.
Good try. though.

535
00:48:57.000 --> 00:48:58.691
No. I see him. There.

536
00:49:03.945 --> 00:49:05.057
Go. Go!

537
00:49:08.361 --> 00:49:10.946
Don't kill him yet. We need information.

538
00:49:22.345 --> 00:49:26.022
Go. Bob. go! Go. Bob. go! Go. Bob. go!

539
00:49:26.506 --> 00:49:29.156
Come here. sweetheart. Get back here.

540
00:49:32.138 --> 00:49:33.633
Come here!

541
00:49:41.930 --> 00:49:43.042
Let go!

542
00:49:45.962 --> 00:49:48.417
- Get the bad lady. Bob.
- Let go!

543
00:49:49.257 --> 00:49:51.331
- Can you hold my turtle?
- Not now.

544
00:49:59.403 --> 00:50:00.963
Yay. Bob!

545
00:50:01.578 --> 00:50:02.691
That's it.

546
00:50:03.467 --> 00:50:04.482
You will pay for that.

547
00:50:04.586 --> 00:50:06.441
- little American princess.
- Bob. help!

548
00:50:22.570 --> 00:50:24.228
Again. again. again.

549
00:50:26.507 --> 00:50:27.434
Okay.

550
00:50:33.163 --> 00:50:36.164
- Why did you pull us out of school?
- Who cares? We're out.

551
00:50:36.300 --> 00:50:38.154
Why are you in the front seat anyway?
It's my day.

552
00:50:38.252 --> 00:50:41.154
- No. it isn't. It's my day.
- No. it's not your day. You're the liar.

553
00:50:41.260 --> 00:50:44.260
- No. today is my day.
- No. today is my day.

554
00:50:44.363 --> 00:50:46.752
- You're a liar.
- No. No. No.

555
00:50:46.860 --> 00:50:49.610
- All right. quiet!
- I'm still hungry.

556
00:50:57.932 --> 00:51:01.063
It doesn't look like
they have chicken tenders here.

557
00:51:01.772 --> 00:51:04.139
Wait inside. I have to make a call.

558
00:51:12.013 --> 00:51:15.329
<i>- This is Firefly.</i>
- This is Bob Ho. I need help.

559
00:51:18.252 --> 00:51:20.488
Yeah. so I get pretty good grades
at this university.

560
00:51:20.589 --> 00:51:24.166
I'm top of the class.
I don't like to brag. but. you know.

561
00:51:24.268 --> 00:51:27.171
- Bob. this is Larry.
- Pleased to meet you. sir.

562
00:51:27.437 --> 00:51:29.858
- Let's get some food.
- He goes to the university.

563
00:51:29.964 --> 00:51:31.972
He's a poet. Isn't it cool?

564
00:51:35.085 --> 00:51:40.486
It's rad. It's awesome. It's jiggy for shizzy.
It's the bomb.

565
00:51:41.772 --> 00:51:43.747
- Let's go.
- Hey!

566
00:51:46.251 --> 00:51:47.779
How embarrassing.

567
00:51:48.140 --> 00:51:50.989
You know. most people don't like me
when they first meet me.

568
00:51:51.085 --> 00:51:52.427
But Larry did.

569
00:51:54.830 --> 00:51:58.245
I have two words for you. Larry. Thirteen.

570
00:52:14.990 --> 00:52:16.397
I have to go.

571
00:52:17.293 --> 00:52:22.083
All right. Nora. Come on.
You two stay at the table.

572
00:52:26.030 --> 00:52:26.979
No. no. no.

573
00:52:28.110 --> 00:52:29.768
I can't go in there.

574
00:52:40.335 --> 00:52:41.763
Boys are pigs.

575
00:52:46.191 --> 00:52:47.335
Careful.

576
00:52:57.294 --> 00:53:00.043
And the lion jumped on me.
and I killed him with my bare hands.

577
00:53:00.143 --> 00:53:01.768
and I saved the colonel's life.

578
00:53:01.871 --> 00:53:03.759
- You're brave.
- Thanks.

579
00:53:05.488 --> 00:53:09.513
How about this. Bob? The whole restaurant
and the waitress sat Larry here.

580
00:53:09.614 --> 00:53:12.463
- Isn't it great?
- It's like it's fate or something.

581
00:53:12.592 --> 00:53:14.697
Really. sir. we're just goofing around.

582
00:53:14.799 --> 00:53:17.385
- Hey. Nora. Knock. knock.
- Who's there?

583
00:53:17.744 --> 00:53:20.045
- Irish stew.
- Irish stew who?

584
00:53:20.527 --> 00:53:22.665
Irish stew in the name of the law.

585
00:53:25.582 --> 00:53:28.714
Larry was telling me all about
the university. It sounds great.

586
00:53:28.814 --> 00:53:31.662
- I'd be glad to give you a tour sometime.
- When pigs fly.

587
00:53:31.759 --> 00:53:33.515
It's not up to you. You're not my dad.

588
00:53:33.614 --> 00:53:37.477
No. but I know that your mother
hasn't completely lost her mind.

589
00:53:37.583 --> 00:53:38.991
It's just a tour. Bob.

590
00:53:39.088 --> 00:53:41.902
It's not like he's asking me out on a date
or anything.

591
00:53:42.001 --> 00:53:43.146
Are you?

592
00:53:44.273 --> 00:53:46.411
No. it's just a friendly offer.

593
00:53:46.511 --> 00:53:49.546
Even if it was a date.
you still couldn't stop me.

594
00:53:54.512 --> 00:53:57.546
- What's your major. Larry?
- English Lit.

595
00:53:57.968 --> 00:54:00.040
Would you pass the soy sauce?

596
00:54:01.072 --> 00:54:03.854
That way I get a background in the classics.

597
00:54:08.944 --> 00:54:12.905
- You speak Russian. Larry?
- What's going on?

598
00:54:31.313 --> 00:54:35.056
- This is going to be painful.
- You're right about that.

599
00:54:38.673 --> 00:54:39.950
Go. go. go.

600
00:54:47.441 --> 00:54:49.645
Maybe you'll write a poem about this.

601
00:54:58.673 --> 00:55:00.082
Goodbye. Larry.

602
00:55:16.114 --> 00:55:17.358
Fine. He's too old for me.

603
00:55:17.457 --> 00:55:21.287
Bob. I don't want to be a princess anymore.
I want to be a cyborg.

604
00:55:22.194 --> 00:55:24.714
How did he find us so fast?
It doesn't make sense.

605
00:55:24.818 --> 00:55:27.502
- Bob. what's going on?
- Please quiet. I'm trying to think.

606
00:55:27.602 --> 00:55:28.879
What do you mean. you're trying to think?

607
00:55:28.977 --> 00:55:31.696
- You just threw a man out the window...
- Who is he? What is...

608
00:55:31.796 --> 00:55:34.032
All right. all right. fine. Fine.

609
00:55:34.931 --> 00:55:39.535
I am international spy. on loan to the CIA
from the Chinese Intelligence Service.

610
00:55:39.635 --> 00:55:43.944
Someone wants me dead.
and "Larry" was a Russian operative. okay?

611
00:55:44.499 --> 00:55:46.157
Fine. Don't tell us.

612
00:55:47.859 --> 00:55:48.907
Cool.

613
00:55:54.099 --> 00:55:55.953
Why would he come alone?

614
00:55:57.523 --> 00:55:58.766
Stay here.

615
00:56:01.874 --> 00:56:03.817
- Where are the kids?
- Inside.

616
00:56:04.147 --> 00:56:06.831
Nothing else matters
until these kids are safe. Nothing.

617
00:56:06.932 --> 00:56:10.227
Of course. Colton set up that safe house
for them like you requested.

618
00:56:10.324 --> 00:56:13.739
- Hey. got that file on you?
- What file?

619
00:56:14.228 --> 00:56:16.847
The one Colton linked you to.
from Poldark's computer. your download.

620
00:56:16.948 --> 00:56:19.882
I didn't download it.
I never even got it open.

621
00:56:20.276 --> 00:56:23.178
Don't BS me. Bob. It's classified material.
I need all copies.

622
00:56:23.285 --> 00:56:25.140
Why would you think I downloaded it?

623
00:56:25.268 --> 00:56:28.300
Unless someone told you I had.
someone who wanted it back.

624
00:56:28.403 --> 00:56:30.411
Let's not make this thing
harder than it has to be. Bob.

625
00:56:30.516 --> 00:56:32.109
Give me the file.

626
00:56:32.212 --> 00:56:34.667
You're a career officer. Why do this?

627
00:56:34.772 --> 00:56:37.357
I want out. Same as you.
We're both leaving for love.

628
00:56:37.460 --> 00:56:40.689
Only I love money
and Anton Poldark is match. Com. The file.

629
00:56:43.638 --> 00:56:46.484
Wait. Take it easy.

630
00:56:53.172 --> 00:56:54.100
Good work.

631
00:56:54.516 --> 00:56:55.445
No.

632
00:57:00.148 --> 00:57:04.557
Can I just say. you are by far
the coolest guy my mom has ever dated.

633
00:57:06.356 --> 00:57:09.139
At least now I know how
that kid Larry found us so fast.

634
00:57:09.237 --> 00:57:10.731
- How?
- The watch.

635
00:57:11.317 --> 00:57:15.114
Glaze told me to keep the watch.
It must have a tracking device.

636
00:57:16.149 --> 00:57:21.387
- Wow. You really are a spy.
- Gillian is totally going to freak.

637
00:57:42.550 --> 00:57:44.306
What are you doing?

638
00:57:44.566 --> 00:57:48.460
There's iron in these rocks.
It will hide the signal. Watch. please.

639
00:57:49.206 --> 00:57:51.572
You realize if I told anyone at school
this story.

640
00:57:51.669 --> 00:57:54.320
I'd get detention for a year for lying.

641
00:58:01.335 --> 00:58:03.723
- Yes.
<i>- Hey. partner. Where're you at?</i>

642
00:58:05.366 --> 00:58:08.879
- Why do you ask?
- I needed to pick up that file I sent you.

643
00:58:08.983 --> 00:58:11.122
<i>You know.</i>
<i>the one I wanted you to open for me.</i>

644
00:58:14.518 --> 00:58:16.274
<i>Bob. you there?</i>

645
00:58:16.406 --> 00:58:19.441
Colton. I never thought
you would have sold out to Poldark.

646
00:58:19.543 --> 00:58:23.917
Hey. that's crazy. man. Something's wrong.
We need to get together and talk.

647
00:58:24.886 --> 00:58:28.432
- Nice try.
- Bob? Bob?

648
00:58:35.352 --> 00:58:40.055
- We'll be safe here. I promise.
- This is your plan? Hide out in a hotel?

649
00:58:40.408 --> 00:58:43.756
Doesn't look like they have
chicken tenders here. either.

650
00:58:59.543 --> 00:59:03.056
This is awesome.
Can we order room service?

651
00:59:03.159 --> 00:59:05.549
- Are you crazy? I'm going home.
- No.

652
00:59:06.104 --> 00:59:09.234
- The only place you're safe is with me.
- Safe with you?

653
00:59:09.335 --> 00:59:12.685
- Everybody's trying to kill you.
- I know. Isn't it cool?

654
00:59:12.889 --> 00:59:17.264
Hey. Bob. if you want to marry my mom.
I'll personally write the invitations.

655
00:59:45.529 --> 00:59:46.936
Love you. Bob.

656
01:00:01.081 --> 01:00:02.642
Be realistic. Bob.

657
01:00:07.577 --> 01:00:08.887
<i>- Hello.</i>
<i>- Hi. Gillian.</i>

658
01:00:08.986 --> 01:00:10.644
<i>Hi. sweetheart.</i>

659
01:00:10.746 --> 01:00:13.112
Yeah. Grandpa just fell asleep.
I was gonna call you guys.

660
01:00:13.945 --> 01:00:16.149
I have to tell you something.

661
01:00:16.250 --> 01:00:19.381
I know this is going to hurt you.
but I have to tell you.

662
01:00:19.481 --> 01:00:21.903
<i>- Are you all right?</i>
- I'm fine.

663
01:00:22.713 --> 01:00:25.136
- It's about Bob.
<i>- What about him?</i>

664
01:00:25.243 --> 01:00:28.657
He's not who you think he is.
He's a spy. a Chinese spy.

665
01:00:28.763 --> 01:00:31.991
And these terrorists are trying to kill him.
and now the CIA's after him. too. and they...

666
01:00:32.090 --> 01:00:35.407
Farren. I know you don't like Bob.
but come on.

667
01:00:35.515 --> 01:00:37.936
<i>I'd expect this from lan. but not from you.</i>

668
01:00:38.042 --> 01:00:41.971
What? No. it's true. He's going
to get us all killed. Don't you even care?

669
01:00:42.330 --> 01:00:45.178
<i>Farren. this conversation is over.</i>
<i>Put Bob on.</i>

670
01:00:52.858 --> 01:00:53.939
Hi. Gillian.

671
01:00:54.043 --> 01:00:57.174
Bob. I am so sorry.
I don't know what's gotten into her.

672
01:00:59.225 --> 01:01:01.082
- It's true.
<i>- What is?</i>

673
01:01:02.811 --> 01:01:04.883
Everything she said is all true.

674
01:01:05.402 --> 01:01:07.705
Whatever this is. it isn't funny.

675
01:01:07.996 --> 01:01:09.556
The kids are safe. I promise.

676
01:01:09.659 --> 01:01:12.375
I'll give them to you
as soon as you get back.

677
01:01:12.796 --> 01:01:16.756
You're either telling me the truth
or I've left my kids with a nut job.

678
01:01:18.683 --> 01:01:21.171
Either way. you should come and get them.

679
01:01:38.139 --> 01:01:42.449
So. you got any other cool spy stuff.
besides the watch?

680
01:01:49.084 --> 01:01:52.084
Don't touch. It's very sharp.

681
01:01:52.924 --> 01:01:54.615
Cool. What else?

682
01:02:05.341 --> 01:02:06.322
Cool.

683
01:02:22.013 --> 01:02:23.419
Sorry. mister.

684
01:02:25.245 --> 01:02:26.772
Airport. Step on it.

685
01:02:47.389 --> 01:02:50.870
- Bob? Are you awake?
- Are you kidding?

686
01:02:52.638 --> 01:02:56.283
- Does he always snore like that?
- Can't you hear him next door?

687
01:02:56.639 --> 01:02:58.940
I always thought it was the pig.

688
01:03:02.141 --> 01:03:04.793
It's over with you and Gillian. isn't it?

689
01:03:06.846 --> 01:03:08.635
Yes. Farren. it's over.

690
01:03:10.142 --> 01:03:13.753
- You win.
- Then why don't I feel like I won?

691
01:03:14.494 --> 01:03:17.876
If you really loved her.
you wouldn't give up this easily.

692
01:03:18.749 --> 01:03:23.704
It's because I love her and the three of you
that I have to walk away.

693
01:03:24.381 --> 01:03:26.869
It's more important that you're safe.

694
01:03:28.512 --> 01:03:31.893
I thought I could put my other life
behind me. but I can't.

695
01:03:32.734 --> 01:03:36.215
Be glad.
You're lucky you're not joining this family.

696
01:03:38.846 --> 01:03:43.386
You've no idea what it's like to live in
a place where you totally don't belong.

697
01:03:43.487 --> 01:03:46.454
Don't be so sure. I was an orphan.

698
01:03:47.007 --> 01:03:51.644
I was raised in a group home.
I never knew my parents. but I had a family.

699
01:03:52.510 --> 01:03:55.413
I had dozens of brothers and sisters there.

700
01:03:55.807 --> 01:03:59.735
And I wasn't related to any of them.
but I loved them all.

701
01:04:02.272 --> 01:04:04.660
Family isn't whose blood you carry.

702
01:04:05.760 --> 01:04:08.510
It's who you love and who loves you.

703
01:04:17.984 --> 01:04:19.390
- Gillian!
- Mom!

704
01:04:26.048 --> 01:04:29.790
Gillian. I'm really sorry about everything.

705
01:04:35.743 --> 01:04:39.224
Tell me the truth. Are you really a spy?

706
01:04:41.217 --> 01:04:45.276
Yes. I am. I was going to tell you at dinner.
but you stopped me.

707
01:04:46.338 --> 01:04:49.817
I don't care. You put my children in danger.

708
01:04:51.008 --> 01:04:52.155
Just go.

709
01:04:58.594 --> 01:05:02.269
Bob. when are we going to see you again?

710
01:05:04.641 --> 01:05:05.785
You're not.

711
01:05:15.680 --> 01:05:20.057
Please don't go away.
Who's gonna sing me China songs?

712
01:05:29.409 --> 01:05:33.086
- You'll be safe. I promise.
- Stay away from my children.

713
01:06:20.642 --> 01:06:24.287
<i>Dear Mom. I am very sorry.</i>
<i>but I cannot stay here.</i>

714
01:06:24.386 --> 01:06:27.452
<i>My destiny is to be a spy. like Bob.</i>

715
01:06:32.067 --> 01:06:36.890
<i>I am going with him.</i>
<i>Best wishes. your son. lan.</i>

716
01:07:17.732 --> 01:07:20.383
Ho's signal just popped back up.
We got him.

717
01:07:22.661 --> 01:07:23.969
Let's roll.

718
01:07:47.878 --> 01:07:50.627
Bob! Bob!

719
01:07:51.749 --> 01:07:53.659
- Lan.
- You left your watch.

720
01:07:54.149 --> 01:07:56.221
What are you doing here? Let's go.

721
01:07:57.317 --> 01:07:59.685
What do you mean? We just got here.

722
01:08:09.669 --> 01:08:14.371
Bob Ho. What a coincidence. Tie them up.

723
01:08:21.541 --> 01:08:24.161
- What are you doing here. lan?
- I'm coming with you.

724
01:08:24.263 --> 01:08:25.637
I want to be a spy. too.

725
01:08:26.982 --> 01:08:30.299
Is this the bad guy?
I thought he'd be better dressed.

726
01:08:32.614 --> 01:08:35.516
- How did you find me?
- I found one of your tracking devices

727
01:08:35.622 --> 01:08:38.111
and put it in your pocket
when I hugged you goodbye.

728
01:08:38.214 --> 01:08:40.286
- I'm impressed.
- Thanks.

729
01:08:40.390 --> 01:08:43.773
- Can we go back to business?
- Would it help to mention I'm retired?

730
01:08:43.878 --> 01:08:46.049
Retired men don't download secrets.

731
01:08:46.150 --> 01:08:48.801
- I never downloaded anything.
- He's lying.

732
01:08:49.927 --> 01:08:52.861
Who are you going to believe?
Me or the traitor?

733
01:08:53.478 --> 01:08:56.675
Someone has been a very naughty boy.

734
01:08:57.574 --> 01:09:01.252
He's got cameras and microphones
mounted all over the place.

735
01:09:01.959 --> 01:09:04.381
Good plan. filming us together.

736
01:09:04.967 --> 01:09:08.000
- How could you turn against your country?
- It's simple.

737
01:09:08.775 --> 01:09:10.466
I'm gonna be a billionaire.

738
01:09:10.568 --> 01:09:15.074
That file that you didn't download?
It's a formula for a Growth Bacteria Hybrid.

739
01:09:15.175 --> 01:09:18.972
This stuff literally eats oil.
Can you imagine?

740
01:09:19.463 --> 01:09:23.173
Overnight.
all the world's oil supplies go poof.

741
01:09:23.272 --> 01:09:26.784
All except for Russia's.
It'll be priceless. right. comrade?

742
01:09:27.590 --> 01:09:29.315
How did you get Colt to go along with you?

743
01:09:29.415 --> 01:09:32.033
Colt? That hillbilly's not part of this.

744
01:09:32.135 --> 01:09:33.727
He doesn't know what goes on
in the real world.

745
01:09:33.831 --> 01:09:35.720
He still thinks wrestling is real.

746
01:09:35.816 --> 01:09:38.434
Let the boy go.
He has nothing to do with this.

747
01:09:38.536 --> 01:09:41.985
Mr. Chit-Chat just laid out our whole plan.

748
01:09:45.928 --> 01:09:47.935
We cannot let him go.

749
01:09:48.392 --> 01:09:52.101
- He will tell.
- Trust me. no one would believe him.

750
01:09:52.680 --> 01:09:54.437
He's right about that.

751
01:09:56.616 --> 01:10:00.162
Hey. boss. Look at what I found
sneaking around outside.

752
01:10:01.096 --> 01:10:03.136
- Farren?
- Hi. everybody.

753
01:10:03.848 --> 01:10:05.757
Please. have a seat.

754
01:10:07.177 --> 01:10:08.605
This can't be happening.

755
01:10:09.832 --> 01:10:14.176
Poldark. let the children go
and I will find this GBH file for you.

756
01:10:14.537 --> 01:10:17.471
GBH? Like. Stockholm GBH?

757
01:10:18.089 --> 01:10:21.156
- How do you know that?
- No freaking way.

758
01:10:21.257 --> 01:10:24.104
You're telling me all of this is
because he downloaded a bootleg concert?

759
01:10:24.201 --> 01:10:25.607
You did what?

760
01:10:26.601 --> 01:10:28.423
You downloaded it?

761
01:10:28.520 --> 01:10:31.335
Wow. these companies take piracy
way too seriously.

762
01:10:31.433 --> 01:10:34.433
You were messing with my computer?
That's private.

763
01:10:34.537 --> 01:10:36.325
I just wanted to seem cool.

764
01:10:36.457 --> 01:10:39.009
You don't need to. You are cool.

765
01:10:39.402 --> 01:10:43.143
- You're one of the coolest kids I know.
- Really? Thanks.

766
01:10:43.241 --> 01:10:46.624
Hey. over here. Man with a gun.

767
01:10:46.921 --> 01:10:50.086
Wait a minute.
I am one of the only kids you know.

768
01:10:51.146 --> 01:10:54.561
- Where is the file?
- It's on my iPod. on my desk at home.

769
01:10:55.562 --> 01:11:00.450
Now. see. you want to be a spy.
Never tell the truth to the bad guy.

770
01:11:00.874 --> 01:11:02.848
Sorry. I'm new at this.

771
01:11:03.306 --> 01:11:07.300
Tatiana. take some men to the kid's house
and find the iPod.

772
01:11:08.170 --> 01:11:10.144
What if the family is home?

773
01:11:11.882 --> 01:11:14.369
Ever since you dyed your hair blonde...
Kill them.

774
01:11:14.474 --> 01:11:17.888
- No. don't!
- Go. bring me that iPod.

775
01:11:18.314 --> 01:11:19.743
Come on. go. Go.

776
01:11:32.203 --> 01:11:34.307
Now. as for you...

777
01:12:06.219 --> 01:12:07.333
Awesome!

778
01:12:22.155 --> 01:12:23.683
Farren. let's go.

779
01:12:25.068 --> 01:12:28.548
- I call dibs on the front.
- Then I pick the radio station.

780
01:12:32.012 --> 01:12:33.320
Okay. Ready?

781
01:12:35.340 --> 01:12:36.746
Okay. hold on.

782
01:12:38.508 --> 01:12:40.581
- Hello?
- Gillian. listen to me.

783
01:12:41.355 --> 01:12:42.665
Goodbye. Bob.

784
01:12:51.085 --> 01:12:53.157
Gillian. wait. Don't hang up.

785
01:12:56.556 --> 01:12:59.458
Hang on.
We've got to get there before they do.

786
01:13:04.652 --> 01:13:08.581
Is there anyone at the agency
you can still trust? Someone you can call?

787
01:13:08.684 --> 01:13:12.099
Sure. but they tore out my cameras.
I have no proof of anything.

788
01:13:12.204 --> 01:13:17.094
Except that. as it happens. I recorded
that entire conversation on my cell phone.

789
01:13:18.957 --> 01:13:20.419
Way to go. dork.

790
01:13:23.246 --> 01:13:27.468
Colt... Just listen.
I'm going to play you something.

791
01:13:29.230 --> 01:13:33.289
<i>That file that you didn't download?</i>
<i>It's a formula for a Growth Bacteria Hybrid.</i>

792
01:13:33.390 --> 01:13:35.627
<i>This stuff literally eats oil.</i>

793
01:13:40.238 --> 01:13:41.186
What is this?

794
01:13:41.294 --> 01:13:43.497
- It's Halloween.
- It's Halloween.

795
01:13:52.686 --> 01:13:54.792
- Happy Halloween.
- Bob!

796
01:13:58.318 --> 01:14:00.773
What are you all doing?
I thought you were upstairs.

797
01:14:01.167 --> 01:14:03.403
- Everybody inside.
- Bob. we need to talk.

798
01:14:03.503 --> 01:14:06.372
Mom. this isn't a joke. Do whatever he says.

799
01:14:07.470 --> 01:14:08.747
- Okay.
- Come on.

800
01:14:09.294 --> 01:14:11.236
- Get your iPod.
- His iPod?

801
01:14:11.342 --> 01:14:13.317
- I demand an explanation.
- They're coming.

802
01:14:13.423 --> 01:14:14.764
- Who?
- The Russians.

803
01:14:14.863 --> 01:14:15.789
Russians?

804
01:14:31.759 --> 01:14:34.061
I saw them outside. They're coming.

805
01:14:34.672 --> 01:14:36.526
- Russians?
- Yes. Gillian. Russians.

806
01:14:36.623 --> 01:14:37.639
Let's try and keep up.

807
01:14:41.167 --> 01:14:44.233
It's too late. Everybody upstairs.
Understand me?

808
01:14:45.455 --> 01:14:46.732
Stay there.

809
01:14:50.736 --> 01:14:51.750
Where's my stuff?

810
01:14:52.239 --> 01:14:54.279
- Here. take some of this stuff.
- What is all this?

811
01:14:54.383 --> 01:14:55.627
Protection.

812
01:14:57.391 --> 01:15:00.206
Why do you have a lighter?
I don't want you playing with fire.

813
01:15:07.952 --> 01:15:10.287
Okay. maybe just this once. Let's go.

814
01:15:10.385 --> 01:15:11.629
Trick or treat.

815
01:15:39.984 --> 01:15:43.247
Hurry. Close it. Close it quick. Okay.

816
01:15:59.345 --> 01:16:01.647
- I forgot Chuckle.
- Nora! Nora!

817
01:16:04.562 --> 01:16:06.022
What are you supposed to be?

818
01:16:06.130 --> 01:16:10.123
A cyborg.
sent from the future to blast you away.

819
01:16:18.513 --> 01:16:20.369
Mommy. that man can fly.

820
01:16:44.626 --> 01:16:48.139
I can't believe you did this to my family.
endangered my kids.

821
01:16:48.242 --> 01:16:50.511
I didn't mean to. I love your kids.

822
01:16:50.609 --> 01:16:53.066
I want to marry you. all four of you.

823
01:16:53.619 --> 01:16:55.145
And I wanted to marry you.

824
01:16:55.250 --> 01:16:57.770
But our wedding gifts would have
to be opened by the bomb squad.

825
01:16:57.876 --> 01:17:00.690
All right. Ho. Enough games.

826
01:17:08.467 --> 01:17:12.177
I finally found a normal guy. I thought.
someone who likes to...

827
01:17:13.907 --> 01:17:15.979
Can we talk about this later?

828
01:17:35.764 --> 01:17:38.132
- He switched belts.
- Get him.

829
01:17:48.180 --> 01:17:50.067
Give me the iPod. kid.

830
01:17:54.675 --> 01:17:58.091
- Come on. let's TP the little geek's house.
- Yeah. TP.

831
01:18:09.331 --> 01:18:10.577
Hey. guys.

832
01:18:12.404 --> 01:18:13.516
Gotta go.

833
01:18:14.005 --> 01:18:16.143
Maybe we should just stick
to stealing candy from little kids.

834
01:18:16.244 --> 01:18:18.000
Yeah. real little kids.

835
01:18:23.285 --> 01:18:26.994
- This is going to be fun.
- Hey. Larry. Knock. knock.

836
01:18:28.948 --> 01:18:29.876
Yes!

837
01:18:46.837 --> 01:18:49.741
Come on. guys. get in the room
and lock the door. Hurry. Lock it.

838
01:19:09.526 --> 01:19:12.209
Irish stew in the name of the law.

839
01:19:13.525 --> 01:19:16.112
Sorry your retirement was so short. Bob.

840
01:19:19.765 --> 01:19:22.667
- You can kill me. Let the family go.
- I can't. They've seen too much.

841
01:19:22.774 --> 01:19:24.662
But I'll let you go first
so you don't have to watch.

842
01:19:24.759 --> 01:19:26.100
Hey. mister.

843
01:19:32.854 --> 01:19:35.092
Don't think this changes anything.

844
01:19:35.478 --> 01:19:38.096
- Everybody freeze!
- It's okay.

845
01:19:38.774 --> 01:19:40.531
They're the good guys.

846
01:19:44.630 --> 01:19:48.046
You stinking lowlife. Come on. Let's go.

847
01:19:52.950 --> 01:19:53.879
Mom!

848
01:20:00.471 --> 01:20:01.900
Hey. loosen these things up.

849
01:20:02.007 --> 01:20:05.171
I'm sorry. What's wrong?
Got the handcuffs too tight?

850
01:20:05.303 --> 01:20:09.100
I don't know how these things work.
I'm just a dumb hillbilly.

851
01:20:10.584 --> 01:20:12.690
- Everybody okay?
- Bumps and bruises.

852
01:20:12.792 --> 01:20:15.159
Lan. this really is the good guy.

853
01:20:17.974 --> 01:20:20.431
Hey. what you got there. son?

854
01:20:22.263 --> 01:20:25.198
Nice work recording that conversation.
partner.

855
01:20:25.400 --> 01:20:28.399
This young man might make
a heck of a spy someday.

856
01:20:37.207 --> 01:20:40.275
How quickly can you give me
orange jumpsuit?

857
01:20:42.201 --> 01:20:43.858
I'm sorry I suspected you.

858
01:20:43.960 --> 01:20:45.749
Don't worry about it. old buddy.

859
01:20:45.849 --> 01:20:48.303
Chalk it up to the language barrier.

860
01:20:48.985 --> 01:20:50.261
Thank you.

861
01:21:02.424 --> 01:21:04.978
I'm sorry I put you through all this.

862
01:21:07.000 --> 01:21:08.593
Goodbye. Gillian.

863
01:21:11.257 --> 01:21:12.751
Goodbye. kids.

864
01:21:15.450 --> 01:21:16.497
Bob.

865
01:21:19.065 --> 01:21:21.073
I'm gonna miss you.

866
01:21:21.177 --> 01:21:22.899
I'll miss you. too.

867
01:21:30.137 --> 01:21:31.414
Wait.

868
01:21:32.729 --> 01:21:35.599
I know he lied. but he did it to protect us.

869
01:21:35.705 --> 01:21:39.415
This whole time. all he ever wanted to do
was protect us. Mom.

870
01:21:40.985 --> 01:21:42.294
And. Mom.

871
01:21:46.744 --> 01:21:50.422
you're never gonna find a man
as good as Bob. never again.

872
01:21:50.521 --> 01:21:51.767
Never.

873
01:21:52.858 --> 01:21:55.509
I never thought I'd say this.

874
01:21:55.610 --> 01:21:57.618
but I agree with Farren.

875
01:22:02.107 --> 01:22:04.113
I suppose you have something to say. too.

876
01:22:04.218 --> 01:22:06.488
I want Bob to be my daddy.

877
01:22:19.450 --> 01:22:23.345
Do you. Gillian. take Bob
to be your lawfully wedded husband?

878
01:22:23.450 --> 01:22:25.206
I do.

879
01:22:25.306 --> 01:22:29.017
And do you. Bob. take Gillian
to be your lawfully wedded wife?

880
01:22:31.803 --> 01:22:32.981
Gillian.

881
01:22:33.883 --> 01:22:36.601
There's one more thing I have to tell you.

882
01:22:37.211 --> 01:22:39.829
My name really isn't Bob.

883
01:22:43.099 --> 01:22:44.593
That's okay.

884
01:22:45.818 --> 01:22:47.096
I do.

885
01:22:47.835 --> 01:22:51.218
I now pronounce you man and wife.
You may kiss the bride.

886
01:23:04.250 --> 01:23:06.935
Ready. And action.

887
01:23:23.389 --> 01:23:24.435
And cut.

888
01:23:31.804 --> 01:23:35.186
No. that man's so crooked.
he could eat nails and...

889
01:23:35.292 --> 01:23:37.114
Maybe he just wanted
to fill up his gas tanks for free.

890
01:23:37.212 --> 01:23:38.160
I can't blame him.

891
01:23:38.267 --> 01:23:41.717
No. that man's so crooked.
he could eat nails and...

892
01:23:45.309 --> 01:23:46.258
Sorry.

893
01:23:46.365 --> 01:23:47.990
Sorry. mister.

894
01:23:59.102 --> 01:24:00.443
All right.

895
01:24:04.446 --> 01:24:05.558
What's going on?

896
01:24:05.661 --> 01:24:08.377
Bob. I don't want to be a princess anymore.

897
01:24:08.477 --> 01:24:10.616
I want to be a...

898
01:24:12.061 --> 01:24:16.151
I'm an international spy. on loan to the CIA
from the Chinese...

899
01:24:16.893 --> 01:24:19.229
From the Chinese intelligent... Intelligent?

900
01:24:19.326 --> 01:24:21.366
- Intelligence.
- Intelligence.

901
01:24:23.230 --> 01:24:26.775
Well. I'll just pick a few things
and move to the house.

902
01:24:26.878 --> 01:24:29.266
- Okay. cut.
- What does it mean?

903
01:24:29.790 --> 01:24:33.652
I am international spy. on loan to the CIA
from the Chinese intelligent...

904
01:24:33.758 --> 01:24:35.383
- What?
- Intelligent.

905
01:24:36.190 --> 01:24:39.987
I've brought down dictators.
How tough to say...

906
01:24:41.117 --> 01:24:42.546
- Yeah.
- Yes?

907
01:24:47.293 --> 01:24:49.531
Maybe you'll write a poem about...

908
01:24:49.630 --> 01:24:51.191
A poem about... A poem.

909
01:24:51.870 --> 01:24:54.291
Maybe you'll write a poem...

910
01:24:54.909 --> 01:24:57.496
Maybe write... I hate English.

911
01:25:06.398 --> 01:25:09.782
If a man marries you.
he marries all four of you.

912
01:25:10.622 --> 01:25:12.761
Don't forget the pig. the cat and the turkey.

913
01:25:12.863 --> 01:25:14.837
And the turkey.

914
01:25:16.767 --> 01:25:19.483
- Turkey? Where's the turkey come from?
- I don't know.

915
01:25:20.127 --> 01:25:23.443
- Yeah. well. my grandmother's... Sorry.
- Okay. cut.

916
01:25:26.367 --> 01:25:28.506
Grandmother's great. He plays...

917
01:25:29.631 --> 01:25:30.678
Let's cut.

918
01:25:30.782 --> 01:25:33.849
When they forget a dialogue.
it makes me happy.

919
01:25:34.784 --> 01:25:38.613
Good work. Come out. Camera needs you.

920
01:25:39.712 --> 01:25:40.890
Come on.

921
01:25:41.280 --> 01:25:42.774
What are we doing?

922
01:25:42.879 --> 01:25:46.175
What are you doing? We're filming.
We're making a movie.

923
01:25:47.840 --> 01:25:49.629
Funny man. Funny man.

924
01:25:50.272 --> 01:25:51.319
A camera mark.

